'''阿斯玛·马夫兹'''（{{lang-en|'''Asmaa Mahfouz'''}}，{{lang-ar|'''أسماء محفوظ'''}}，{{bd|1985年|2月1日|||Mahfouz, Asmaa}}），埃及女性人权活动家，是[[2011年埃及革命|2011年埃及革命]]中[[4月6日青年运动|4月6日青年运动]]的发起人<ref name='NYT110202'>{{cite news | first = Mona | last = El-Naggar | title = Equal rights takes to the barricades | date = 1 February 2011 | url = http://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/02/world/middleeast/02iht-letter02.html | work = The New York Times | accessdate = 6 February 2011 | archive-date = 2011-09-07 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110907005214/http://www.nytimes.com/2011/02/02/world/middleeast/02iht-letter02.html | dead-url = no }}</ref>：她在运动爆发之前一周的1月18日通过发布网络视频号召人民参与示威<ref>{{cite news | title = Women play vital role in Egypt's uprising | url = http://www.npr.org/2011/02/04/133497422/Women-Play-Vital-Role-In-Egypts-Uprising | date = 4 February 2011 | work = National Public Radio | format = transcript | accessdate = 6 February 2011 | archive-date = 2011-02-05 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110205032511/http://www.npr.org/2011/02/04/133497422/Women-Play-Vital-Role-In-Egypts-Uprising | dead-url = no }}</ref><ref>{{cite news | title = Revolutionary blogger Asma threatened | date = 5 February 2011 | url = http://gulfnews.com/news/region/egypt/revolutionary-blogger-asma-threatened-1.757171 | work = Gulf News | accessdate = 6 February 2011 | archive-date = 2011-02-22 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110222070019/http://gulfnews.com/news/region/egypt/revolutionary-blogger-asma-threatened-1.757171 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。她是{{le|革命青年聯盟|Coalition of the Youth of the Revolution}}的主要成员以及革命期间的领袖之一<ref> {{cite news | first = Heba | last = Fahmy | title = Youth Coalition says army agrees to remove cabinet and other demands | date = 1 March 2011 | url = http://www.thedailynewsegypt.com/egypt/youth-coalition-says-army-agrees-to-remove-cabinet-and-other-demands.html | work = Daily News Egypt / International Herald Tribune | accessdate = 4 March 2011 | deadurl = yes | archiveurl = https://web.archive.org/web/20110307145615/http://www.thedailynewsegypt.com/egypt/youth-coalition-says-army-agrees-to-remove-cabinet-and-other-demands.html | archivedate =2011-03-07}}</ref>。

2011年10月27日，她与另外其他阿拉伯国家的四人因促进本国的人权与自由而获得[[欧洲议会|欧洲议会]]颁发的[[萨哈罗夫奖|萨哈罗夫奖]]。

== 生平 ==
她生于1985年，毕业于[[开罗大学|开罗大学]]商学院<ref name='aawsat110207'>{{cite news | first = Essam | last = Fadl | title = A talk with Egyptian activist Asmaa Mahfouz | date = 7 February 2011 | url = http://aawsat.com/english/news.asp?section=3&id=24073 | work = Asharq Al-Awsat | accessdate = 7 February 2011 | archive-date = 2011-03-01 | archive-url = https://web.archive.org/web/20110301173955/http://www.aawsat.com/english/news.asp?section=3&id=24073 | dead-url = no }}</ref>。目前在一家计算机公司任职<ref>{{cite web |url=http://www.illumemag.com/zine/articleDetail.php?Egyptian-Youth-Inspired-by-Tunisian-Revolution-Hope-to--Follow-Suit-13452 |title=Thousands Fill the Streets in Egypt Protests |publisher=Illume |accessdate=3 February 2011 |deadurl=yes |archiveurl=https://archive.is/20130103123633/http://www.illumemag.com/zine/articleDetail.php?Egyptian-Youth-Inspired-by-Tunisian-Revolution-Hope-to--Follow-Suit-13452 |archivedate=2013-01-03}}</ref>。

